<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-059-029 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 407 583</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Sept 16 1991 v10 n19 p104(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Perturbed by 'best-value' rule, Glenn asks GAO to audit TMAC. (USSenator John Glenn asks the General Accounting Office to reviewthe Internal Revenue Service's best-value evaluation criteria forthe $1.4 billion Treasury Multiuser Acquisition Contract awardedto ATandamp;T) (Brief Article)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     Competitive BiddingGovernment ContractsContract ProtestsEquipment AcquisitionGovernment RegulationInvestigationsUnited States. Internal Revenue ServiceUnited States. General Accounting Office.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Disturbed by the Internal Revenue Service's use of &quot;best-value&quot; evaluationcriteria for its award of the $1.4 billion Treasury Multiuser Acquisitioncontract to ATandamp;T Co., Sen.andP;  John Glenn has asked the General AccountingOffice to review the buy.andM;The Ohio Democrat's audit request comes in the midst of TMAC bid protestproceedings at the General Services Administration Board of Contract Appeals.andO;The board held a series of closed hearings late last month on protestsbrought by losing bidders IBM Corp. and Lockheed Corp.andM;IRS officials awarded TMAC to ATandamp;T in June.andP;  But IBM and Lockheed protestedthe deal, charging that IRS never revealed its true evaluation scheme.andP;  Theprotesters said they complied with all the mandatory specifications andsubmitted bids that were nearly $500,000 lower than the ATandamp;T proposal.andM;The board is expected to issue its decision this month.andM;Congressional sources said Glenn wants to know why IRS officials ratedbidders according to how well they exceeded the minimum requirements.andP;  Glenn,chairman of the Senate Governmental Affairs Committee, also has voicedconcern about agencies using best-value procurements to justify higher costs.andM;GAO's Information Management and Technology Division is conducting the audit.andO;</TEXT></DOC>